  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// WHAT IT DOES</h3>
    <p>Gives you a single source of truth you never have to assemble: one table that stays current, carries no duplicates, and reads identically everywhere your team looks.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// HOW IT WORKS</h3>
    <p>Each source is pulled on a set schedule and its mismatched fields are mapped into one shared shape, then enriched with common reference data. Every record gets a stable key, and that key drives an upsert -- so each run updates the rows that already exist instead of appending fresh copies. If a pull comes back empty, the run halts and raises a flag rather than overwriting good data with nothing.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// GOOD TO KNOW</h3>
    <p>A backend automation -- there is nothing to operate here. The demo runs on synthetic banking records and keeps a Google Sheet and an Airtable base in lockstep, posting a short summary to a team chat after every run.</p>
  </section>

</div>
